attributes.name: PPSX
attributes.documentation: document msoffice presentation powerpoint slideshow ppsx

attributes.name: malicious
attributes.documentation: Number of antivirus engines that detected the file as malicious.

attributes.name: undetected
attributes.documentation: Number of antivirus engines that didn't detected the file.

attributes.name: failure
attributes.documentation: Number of antivirus engines that failed scanning the file.

attributes.name: type_unsupported
attributes.documentation: Number of antivirus engines that don't support the file's type.

attributes.name: exiftool
attributes.documentation: Dictionary that contains the information generated by ExifTool for the file being scanned. Both keys and values are strings. ExifTool generates numeric values for some properties, but values in YARA dictionaries must have the same time, therefore they are converted to strings.

attributes.name: first_submission_date
attributes.documentation: Date on which the file was submitted to VirusTotal for the first time, as a UNIX timestamp.

attributes.name: file_name
attributes.documentation: File's name as it was last submitted to VirusTotal.

attributes.name: file_type
attributes.documentation: One of the types listed in the file types table (vt.FileType).

attributes.name: file_type_tags
attributes.documentation: Tags associated to the file's type, as listed in the file types table.

attributes.name: version
attributes.documentation: Version of the Golang compiler used.

attributes.name: arch
attributes.documentation: Target architecture for a Golang binary.

attributes.name: os
attributes.documentation: Target OS for a Golang binary.

attributes.name: version
attributes.documentation: Version of the dependency package used.

attributes.name: settings
attributes.documentation: Dictionary where keys are setting names and values are the setting value.

attributes.name: num_dependencies
attributes.documentation: Total number of dependencies for a Golang binary.

attributes.name: num_interfaces
attributes.documentation: Total number of interfaces in a Golang binary.

attributes.name: num_types
attributes.documentation: Total number of types in a Golang binary.

attributes.name: num_std_functions
attributes.documentation: Number of functions from standard library used by a Golang binary.

attributes.name: num_user_functions
attributes.documentation: Number of user-defined functions in a Golang binary.

attributes.name: new_file
attributes.documentation: (Boolean) True if the file is being submitted to VirusTotal for the first time.

attributes.name: magic
attributes.documentation: File's type as returned by Linux's file command.

attributes.name: dhash
attributes.documentation: Hash that clusters together files with similar icons or thumbnails.

attributes.name: raw_md5
attributes.documentation: MD5 of the icon associated to the file.

attributes.name: malware_families
attributes.documentation: List of family names produced from a malware config extraction process. Samples with malware configs can be obtained searching have:malware_config, family names will be displayed in the detections tab under "Malware config detection" or in the details tab under "Malware configuration file" where there is the full report.

attributes.name: signatures
attributes.documentation: Dictionary where keys are antivirus names and values are malware signatures. The casing for both antivirus names and signatures is exactly as they appear in the web reports or API responses.

attributes.name: subfile
attributes.documentation: (Boolean) True if the file being scanned is not the one submitted to VirusTotal but one derived from it. For example, when a PE file packed with UPX is submitted to VirusTotal, both the original file and the unpacked file are scanned. This is true for the unpacked file and false for the original packed one.

attributes.name: city
attributes.documentation: City from where the file was submitted, referred to the last submission. All lowercases.

attributes.name: country
attributes.documentation: Country from where the file was submitted, referred to the last submission. This is a two-letter ISO 3166 country code, in uppercase.

attributes.name: times_submitted
attributes.documentation: Number of times the file has been submitted to VirusTotal. This is 1 for the first submission.

attributes.name: unique_sources
attributes.documentation: Number of unique sources that have submitted this file.

attributes.name: calls_highlighted
attributes.documentation: API calls that are worth remarking because they are suspicious (e.g. "android.media.AudioRecord.startRecording", "GetTickCount").

attributes.name: text_highlighted
attributes.documentation: Text that can provide further context about the file, this might be windows titles, dialogs, outputs streams, etc.

attributes.name: text_decoded
attributes.documentation: Strings that are either encoded or decoded during the observed time frame, we just record the decoded strings in plain form.

attributes.name: traits
attributes.documentation: List that contains a subset of the values listed in the behaviour traits table.

attributes.name: verdicts
attributes.documentation: Some sandboxes produce a verdict based on the file behaviour. This list contains one or more of the values listed in the behaviour verdicts table.

attributes.name: verdicts_labels
attributes.documentation: List that contains the verdicts labels based on the file behaviour sandboxes.

attributes.name: mitre_attack_techniques
attributes.documentation: String containing the mitre attack techniques.

attributes.name: files_attribute_changed
attributes.documentation: Paths of the files whose attributes have changed.

attributes.name: files_copied
attributes.documentation: Structures with information about files that have been copied.

attributes.name: source
attributes.documentation: Path where the file was copied from.

attributes.name: destination
attributes.documentation: Path where the file was copied to.

attributes.name: files_deleted
attributes.documentation: Paths of the files that have been deleted.

attributes.name: files_dropped
attributes.documentation: Structures with information about files that have been dropped.

attributes.name: files_opened
attributes.documentation: Paths of the files that have been opened.

attributes.name: files_written
attributes.documentation: Paths of the files that have been written.

attributes.name: hostname
attributes.documentation: Hostname in the DNS lookup request.

attributes.name: List of IP address returned for the requested hostname.
attributes.documentation: List of IP address returned for the requested hostname.

attributes.name: destination_ip_as_int
attributes.documentation: Destination IP address dotless decimal number notation.

attributes.name: transport_layer_protocol
attributes.documentation: One of the constants listed in network protocols (vt.Net.Protocol).

attributes.name: request_method
attributes.documentation: One of the constants listed in vt.Http.Method.

attributes.name: request_headers
attributes.documentation: HTTP request headers. Notice that dictionary keys are case-sensitive and therefore request_headers["user-agent"] is not the same than request_headers["User-Agent"]. The header name appears as reported by the sandbox.

attributes.name: response_headers
attributes.documentation: HTTP response headers. Notice that dictionary keys are case-sensitive and therefore request_headers["user-agent"] is not the same than request_headers["User-Agent"]. The header name appears as reported by the sandbox.

attributes.name: response_status_code
attributes.documentation: HTTP status code returned by the server.

attributes.name: response_body_filetype
attributes.documentation: HTTP status code returned by the server.

attributes.name: hostname
attributes.documentation: Host name of the SMTP server.

attributes.name: destination_ip
attributes.documentation: IP address of the SMTP server.

attributes.name: destination_port
attributes.documentation: Port number of the SMTP server (usually 25).

attributes.name: smtp_from
attributes.documentation: MAIL FROM: field in the SMTP protocol.

attributes.name: smtp_to
attributes.documentation: MAIL TO: field in the SMTP protocol.

attributes.name: x_mailer
attributes.documentation: Program used for sending the email. Same than "X-Mailer" header.

attributes.name: command_executions
attributes.documentation: Commands executed, including their command-line arguments.

attributes.name: modules_loaded
attributes.documentation: Modules or libraries dynamically loaded (e.g. DLLs loaded with LoadLibrary in Windows, DEX and .class files dynamically loaded in Android).

attributes.name: processes_injected
attributes.documentation: Processes in which some kind of code was injected. For instance, in Window this is commonly done using CreateRemoteThread.

attributes.name: processes_terminated
attributes.documentation: Processes that terminated during the observed time, not necessarily killed.

attributes.name: signals_hooked
attributes.documentation: Signals hooked. In Windows this includes the windows messages hooked with SetWindowsHook and the string contains both the hook type and the function used (i.e "WH_KEYBOARD - SetWindowsHook").

attributes.name: signals_observed
attributes.documentation: From the signals hooked which were actually observed.

attributes.name: services_bound
attributes.documentation: Service binding applies only to Android. A bind operation takes a component, an action, and potentially multiple extras.

attributes.name: services_created
attributes.documentation: Services created. In some OSes services are simply any program that runs in the background without user interaction.

attributes.name: registry_keys_set
attributes.documentation: Modified registry keys and their new values.

attributes.name: shared_preferences_lookups
attributes.documentation: Shared preferences that have been read.

attributes.name: shared_preferences_sets
attributes.documentation: Shared preferences that have been modified.

attributes.name: system_property_lookups
attributes.documentation: System properties that have been read.

attributes.name: system_property_sets
attributes.documentation: System properties that have been modified.

attributes.name: windows_hidden
attributes.documentation: Information about windows that have been hidden. The string contains the caption of the hidden Window and the name of the process owning the window.

attributes.name: windows_searched
attributes.documentation: Windows that have been searched for (e.g. using FindWindow). The strings can contain the window's name, the window's class name, or both.

attributes.name: path
attributes.documentation: Path part of the current URL.

attributes.name: hostname
attributes.documentation: Hostname part of the current URL.

attributes.name: new_url
attributes.documentation: (Boolean) Wether the URL is observed for the first time or not.

attributes.name: first_submission_date
attributes.documentation: UNIX UTC timestamp for the URL's first submission date.

attributes.name: port
attributes.documentation: The port in which the URL is accessed.

attributes.name: trackers
attributes.documentation: All trackers found in the URL.

attributes.name: url
attributes.documentation: URL the tracker is loaded from.

attributes.name: response_headers
attributes.documentation: Headers returned when making a request to the URL.

attributes.name: response_code
attributes.documentation: HTTP status code seen when making a request to the URL.

attributes.name: raw_md5
attributes.documentation: MD5 hash of the URL's favicon. To find a property raw md5 search VT for its URL and check details. Retrieving raw_md5.

attributes.name: dhash
attributes.documentation: The URL's favicon dhash. To find a property dhash search VT for its URL and check details. Retrieving dhash.

attributes.name: outgoing_links
attributes.documentation: Links included in the URLs response pointing to URLs from other domains.

attributes.name: redirects
attributes.documentation: List of redirecting URLs visited until reaching the final one.

attributes.name: html_title
attributes.documentation: Text found under the URLs returned HTML <title> tag.

attributes.name: html_meta_tags
attributes.documentation: Values found under the meta tags in the returned HTML.

attributes.name: tags
attributes.documentation: Tags defining interesting features of the URL.

attributes.name: confirmed_timeout
attributes.documentation: Amount of engine returning confirmed timeout in the analysis.

attributes.name: failure
attributes.documentation: Amount of engine that failed during the analysis process.

attributes.name: type_unsupported
attributes.documentation: Amount of engine that do not support the file/IoC type.

attributes.name: categories
attributes.documentation: Content categories of its domain by engine.

attributes.name: downloaded_file
attributes.documentation: Metadata from the latest file downloaded from the URL.

attributes.name: new_for_vt
attributes.documentation: (Boolean) Indicates that the file has not been previously seen in VT.

attributes.name: new_for_url
attributes.documentation: (Boolean) Indicates that the file has not been previously seen being downloaded from that particular URL.

attributes.name: new_for_domain
attributes.documentation: (Boolean) Indicates that the file has not been previously seen being downloaded from the URLs domain.

attributes.name: new_for_ip
attributes.documentation: (Boolean) Indicates that the file has not been previously seen being downloaded from the IP the URL resolves to.

attributes.name: file_type
attributes.documentation: Latest downloaded file's type (one of the types listed in the file types table).

attributes.name: analysis_stats
attributes.documentation: Latest downloaded file analysis stats. Analysis Stats Struct info.
